The average power density of global marine ecosystems (Pg) was calculated according to the combustion heat of net primary production (NPP) in the oceans. Annual NPP in the oceans was estimated to correspond to 48.5 Pg of carbon per year3. The elemental composition of carbon in organic matter was estimated to be 50%, and the heating value of organic matter was estimated to be 20 kJ/g in a recent study65. The area of global oceans is ~3.625 × 108 square kilometers67. The calculation of Pg refers to Eq. (5):5Pg=2×48.5×1015×20000365×86400×3.625×1014=0.169W⋅m−2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
